      "writtenOn": "2014-05-28T21:48:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok... OF does something like this:\nif !(PLL_CONTROL \u0026 0x80000000) adcdata[channel] -\u003d 0x1a;\nIf you\u0027re sure that PLL control doesn\u0027t change, it always substracts 0x1a. In this case it would not produce an additional cut off. Now, if your formula is precise enough, there is no need to do it at all. So i propose to discard this condition, if the PLL control really doesn\u0027t change (i\u0027m too lazy to check it :P).",
      "parentUuid": "9abe1de1_9ae1a901",
      "revId": "f1120de011cc7e9a104208ba881020f3dc3f54dd",
